20/11/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- NATO Secretary General Lord George Robertson appointed former Turkish Foreign Minister and Parliament Speaker Hikmet Cetin as Alliance political representative in Afghanistan on Wednesday (19 November). 
In an official statement, Ankara commended the decision and offered full support for Cetin's future activities. 
The statement also commended NATO's role in Afghanistan, describing its presence as an important step towards the restoration of security there. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV - 19/11/03)
